    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri dei et salvatori nostri Iesu Christi. Anno ab
                        incarnatione eiusdem millesimo centesimo sesto decimo, tercio Henrico
                        imperante anno sesto, octavo idus iulii, indictione nona. Dum esset
                        <persName key="#Missus_regis" ref="#people/1261">Iohannes Boitane</persName>
                        <rs key="#Missus_regis">misso</rs> domni Henrici <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >imperatoris</rs> in <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/1566"><geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/1126"
                                >Celula</geogName></placeName> in loco, qui vocatur
                            <placeName>Runcus Domnicus</placeName> iusta <rs key="#Roads">stratha
                                que vocatur Cluza</rs>, et simul cum eo domnus <persName><name key="#Monks"
                                ref="Lanfrancus">Lanfrancus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> sicque <persName><name key="#Viscount"
                                ref="Albericus">Albericus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Viscount" >vicecomitis</rs> seu <persName><name ref="Ildeprandus"
                                >Ildeprandus</name></persName> filius <persName><name
                                ref="Ildeprandus">Ildeprandi</name></persName> namque
                                <persName><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Severus">Severo</name></persName> et
                                <persName><name ref="Albertus/Candidus">Alberto
                            Candidus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Azo" >Azo</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name ref="Wulferius">Golfero</name></persName> et <rs key="#Priest">presbiter</rs>
                        <persName><name key="#Priest" ref="Iohannellus">Gianellus</name></persName> de <rs key="#Castle">castro</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Castle #Priest" ref="#places/1575">Gipso</placeName> et
                                <persName><name>Ragimundus</name></persName> de
                                <persName><name>Sandoni</name></persName> et
                                <persName><name>Tetelmus</name></persName> filius
                                <persName><name>Gaurini</name></persName> de <rs key="#Vici"
                            >vico</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Vici" ref="#places/1583">Petrosa</placeName> et alii plures, in
                        presentia suprascriptorum hominum venerunt hominibus habitatores in castro
                        Gipso, quorum nomina <persName><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        de <persName><name ref="Ioseph">Ioseph</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Albertus/Perdutus">Albertus, qui vocatur
                            Perduto</name></persName>, et <persName><name ref="Constantinus"
                                >Constantinus</name></persName> filius <persName><name
                                ref="Constantinus">Constantini</name></persName>. Fecerunt finem et
                        perpetuam transactionem pro ipsis et eorum consortes in manu prelibati
                        Iohannis misso imperiali vice aecclesie <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/47"
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Missus_of_other_public_authorities">sancti Silvestri</orgName>
                        sito <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/15">Nonantule</placeName> de omnibus illis
                        rebus territoriis, que ispi dicebant infra pertinentiis curte <placeName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#places/2480"><geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/1127"
                            >Ragigose</geogName></placeName> ex datione hominum <rs key="#Countess"
                            >comitipse</rs>
                        <persName key="#Countess" ref="#people/125">Matilde</persName>, qui ipsis dicebant eis date
                        essent per <rs key="#Servitium">wardam</rs>
                        roce
                        <placeName key="#Servitium" ref="#places/1576">Gipsadelli</placeName>. Quas iam dicta
                        comitipsa Matilda ante eorum dationem per cartam proprietatis dedit in
                        predicta ecclesia sancti Silvestri in restauratione thesauri, quem ipsa
                        tulit suprascripte aecclesie, et nec <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        suprascripti monasterii nec alius suus <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missus</rs> concessit neque
                        confirmavit in dactione, quem fecerunt suprascripti homines Matilde in
                        predictis hominibus Gipsi. Et si suprascriptam transactionem non
                        observaverint, incidant in penam et bannum imperatoris. Et in suprascriptam
                        penam promiserunt dare et conducere omne <rs key="#Rent_in_kind"
                            >redditum</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cereals">blavis</rs> de iam dicta terra secundum consuetudinem
                        loci ad <rs key="#Hospitals">hospicium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rent_in_kind #Cereals #Hospitals">Lavini</placeName>. Et si in aliquo tempore ostendunt iusta legem
                        habere pertinentiam, in suprascriptis rebus observetur eis. Omnes
                        suprascritpi homines rogati sunt testes. In dei nomine ego + <persName><name key="#Notary"
                                ref="Albertus">Albertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scripsi hec.</ab>
